definition.value: A carbohydrazide that is L-tryptophan in which the amino and carboxy groups are substituted by tert-butoxycarbonyl and 2-({[2-(2-ethylanilino)-2-oxoethyl]sulfanyl}carbonyl)hydrazinyl groups, respectively. It is a potent and reversible inhibitor of human cathepsin L (IC50 = 56 nM).

A branched amino trisaccharide consisting of at the reducing end an N-acetyl-6-sulfo-beta-D-galactosamine residue to which are linked alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl residues via (1->3) and (1->4) glycosidic linkages respectively.

A branched amino trisaccharide consisting of at the reducing end an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue to which are linked alpha-L-fucosyl and N-acetyl-3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosaminyl residues via (1->3) and (1->4) glycosidic linkages respectively.
A (3'->5')-dinucleotide composed from cytidine and guanosine units.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of sch 210972 resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy and hydroxy groups. Major microspecies at pH 7.3.
The hydrochloride salt of mefuparib. It is a potent poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase inhibitor which exhibits strong anticancer activity and also inhibits SARS-CoV-2 in cell culture.

A member of the class of phenanthridines that is 5,6-dihydrophenanthridine substituted at positions 2 and 6 by (N,N-dimethylglycyl)amino and oxo groups, respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of poly(ADP-ribose) polymerases PARP1 and PARP2 (IC50 of 110 nM and 86 nM, respectively) and exhibits anti-cancer, cardioprotective and neuroprotective properties.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear tetrasaccharide unit consisting of N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and (at the reducing end) N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked in sequence (1->3), (1->3) and (1->6), to the beta-galactosyl residue is linked also (1->2) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue.
A tertiary ammonium ion obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino group of PJ34. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A hydrochloride salt prepared from equimolar amounts of PJ34 and hydrochloric acid.

A member of the class of 1-benzofurans that is 1-benzofuran substituted by 4-[(methylamino)methyl]phenyl, fluoro and aminocarbonyl groups at positions 2, 5, and 7, respectively. It is a potent inhibitor of poly(ADP-ribose) polymerases PARP1 and PARP2 (IC50 of 3.2 nM and 1.9 nM, respectively). The compound exhibits anti-cancer properties and has also shown promising antiviral activity against the virus that causes COVID-19.
A secondary ammonium ion resulting from the protonation of the secondary amino group of mefuparib. The major species at pH 7.3.
A cardiolipin where one of the acyl chains is the oxidized fatty acyl chain  9-hydroxy-(10E,12Z)-octadecadienoyl and the other 3 are not defined.
A meroterpenoid with formula C25H34O6 isolated from the fungus Aspergillus novofumigatus. It is an intermediate produced in the biosynthetic pathway leading to the synthesis of novofumigatonin.
Based on the structure elucidated in pmid:26360642 for sch 210972 as it is synthesized from the same precursor as described in pmid:25885659
